**Original author :** Blatti Yves

Hi Jérôme,

We talked about the code highlight in the forge "this morning":https://forge.easysdi.org/projects/joomla/wiki/Meeting_26th_june_2015.
Here is the reason why it is not active in the forge:

The template of the forge should override redmine CSS classes. But it does not include the base classes.

You can use our forge as an example:

This is our template:
https://projets.asitvd.ch/themes/asitvd/stylesheets/application.css

as you can see is refers to redmine default template:
```

@import url(../../../stylesheets/application.css);
```


This file exists in easysdi forge's install: https://forge.easysdi.org/stylesheets/application.css
And contains coderay classes:

```

<code class="css">
/************* CodeRay styles *************/
.syntaxhl div {display: inline;}
.syntaxhl .line-numbers {padding: 2px 4px 2px 4px; background-color: #eee; margin:0px 5px 0px 0px;}
.syntaxhl .code pre { overflow: auto }
.syntaxhl .debug { color: white !important; background: blue !important; }

```



*So this line should do the trick* at the top of : https://forge.easysdi.org/themes/easysdi/stylesheets/application.css

```

@import url(../../../stylesheets/application.css);
```
